Ok, Doc,<br><br>
Wipe your *feet* at the door, especially after one of those cow flop squishing dances you folks out by the San Andreas fault are so fond of. Chubby Checker tried &quot;Let's Do the Fault!&quot;, but that dance didn't catch on. I guess there is too much of the real thing in those parts.<br><br>
Anyway, since there isn't much hope, the whole mess is going to seceede from the union in a few hundred thousand years or so and drift off to its well deserved oblivion in some subduction trench at the bottom of the pacific. That will really be progress!<br><br>
I'll be off line for two weeks visiting the homeland, Italy, that is. There is a small village, Celenza Valfortore, between Napoli and Foggia in the mountains, where my family still lives. We were real swingers in Rome in the feudal middle ages and the Rennaisance. I guess I will have to get some pointers from the old boys on how we handled serfs, peasants, and other unmentionables back then. It probably still runs in the family.<br><br>
Well, Doc, take care until I return, and please do not continue to try to connect my behavior with yours. There is really no connection, whatever. Misery may love company, but I personally find the smell of cow flops repulsive!   
